retty large on me, these were actually somewhat small, so be aware of that when ordering.  My toe comes right to the edge with my heel only having about 1/4 of an inch or less of space from the back of the flop and again, I\'m an 11.5 and these are rated 12/14 M. So these run small and narrow.One word of caution, however: One common problem with Havianas is that like flip flops from the 70s, the toe part that clips into the bottom of the shoe will slip loose as they wear.  So don\'t run in them, as this may happen while you are running and you could trip.  I will attach a photo of what I mean.  This tends to happen to me if I do more than just very casually walk in this type of flop or if the ground is really hot as it gets here in DC in the summer on the roads.','I620694861'),(1028,'2012-01-12',5,'Perfect Thermals','[[\'Clothing, Shoes & Jewelry\', \'C\', \'Carhartt\'], [\'Clothing, Shoes & Jewelry\', \'Men\', \'Clothing\', \'Underwear\', \'Thermal Underwear\', \'Bottoms\'], [\'Clothing, Shoes & Jewelry\', \'Men\', \'Big & Tall\']]','I bought these for my husband for our trip to the mountains in GA for Christams. He loves them and wants more. We highly recommend them.','I200025341'),(1029,'2013-10-24',2,'Not for me','[[\'Clothing, Shoes & Jewelry\', \'C\', \'Calvin Klein\'], [\'Clothing, Shoes & Jewelry\', \'Men\', \'Clothing\', \'Underwear\', \'Boxer Briefs\']]','Granny Panties for the man.  I bought these to try an alternative to traditional woven boxer shorts and although they fit well when you first put them on, they are a knit cotton fabric and stretch way out (especially the leg openings) after a short while of wearing them. That makes them bulky and loose and all bunched up and uncomfortable under your pants. Also they are a heavier thicker cotton and feel too hot in the summer. When they get sweaty and then hold the moisture It\'s like having a wet facecloth in your crotch. I bought both the black and grey ones and after a couple of washes you could see the